 129:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   /* This variable is updated in three ways:
 130:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****       1) by calling CMSIS function SystemCoreClockUpdate()
 131:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****       2) by calling HAL API function HAL_RCC_GetHCLKFreq()
 132:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****       3) each time HAL_RCC_ClockConfig() is called to configure the system clock frequency 
 133:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****          Note: If you use this function to configure the system clock; then there
 134:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****                is no need to call the 2 first functions listed above, since SystemCoreClock
 135:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****                variable is updated automatically.
 136:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   */
