 186:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c **** /**
 187:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****    * @brief  Update SystemCoreClock variable according to Clock Register Values.
 188:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *         The SystemCoreClock variable contains the core clock (HCLK), it can
 189:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *         be used by the user application to setup the SysTick timer or configure
 190:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *         other parameters.
 191:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *           
 192:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   * @note   Each time the core clock (HCLK) changes, this function must be called
 193:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *         to update SystemCoreClock variable value. Otherwise, any configuration
 194:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *         based on this variable will be incorrect.         
 195:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *     
 196:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   * @note   - The system frequency computed by this function is not the real 
 197:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *           frequency in the chip. It is calculated based on the predefined 
 198:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *           constant and the selected clock source:
 199:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *             
 200:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *           - If SYSCLK source is HSI, SystemCoreClock will contain the HSI_VALUE(*)
 201:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *                                              
 202:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *           - If SYSCLK source is HSE, SystemCoreClock will contain the HSE_VALUE(**)
 203:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *                          
 204:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *           - If SYSCLK source is PLL, SystemCoreClock will contain the HSE_VALUE(**) 
 205:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *             or HSI_VALUE(*) multiplied/divided by the PLL factors.
 206:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *         
 207:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *         (*) HSI_VALUE is a constant defined in stm32f4xx_hal_conf.h file (default value
 208:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *             16 MHz) but the real value may vary depending on the variations
 209:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *             in voltage and temperature.   
 210:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *    
 211:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *         (**) HSE_VALUE is a constant defined in stm32f4xx_hal_conf.h file (its value
 212:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *              depends on the application requirements), user has to ensure that HSE_VALUE
 213:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *              is same as the real frequency of the crystal used. Otherwise, this function
 214:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *              may have wrong result.
 215:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *                
 216:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *         - The result of this function could be not correct when using fractional
 217:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *           value for HSE crystal.
 218:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *     
 219:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   * @param  None
 220:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   * @retval None
 221:Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32F4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   */
